1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:00:10,490 --> 00:00:15,320
Go! Go! Zoro! What's the hold up?!
Get moving and pound them!

3
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:18,260
You all should pipe down
and go hide somewhere!

4
00:00:19,350 --> 00:00:21,920
Can you guys
make this fun for me?

5
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:33,680
Go, Zoro! This is
your only strength, right?!

6
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:43,690
Hurry up and finish off...
those... ugly-looking...

7
00:00:45,070 --> 00:00:46,940
What do you think
you're doing? Huh?!

8
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:52,570
First rule in the guide to killing:
Start by eliminating the weaker targets.

9
00:00:52,570 --> 00:00:54,910
Let us show you how a pro works.

10
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,870
M-Me?

11
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:04,340
J-Just a minute! There's no point
in getting rid of me.

12
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:07,600
I can beat anyone in looks and style,
but I lack in the ability department.

13
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:08,760
I'm not a fighter.

14
00:01:09,250 --> 00:01:11,300
Didn't we make ourselves clear?

15
00:01:11,650 --> 00:01:15,080
Picking you off first will be
the fastest way to get the job done.

16
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:27,190
I told you to shut up
and hide somewhere.

17
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:21,010
She Who Controls the Weather

18
00:03:22,310 --> 00:03:27,390
Luffy's dead...? I won't
believe such nonsense!

19
00:03:27,390 --> 00:03:29,110
It's quite the opposite.

20
00:03:30,490 --> 00:03:35,440
Straw Hat is buried in the sands
of Rainbase, Miss Wednesday.

21
00:03:39,170 --> 00:03:45,250
Had he not joined in your meddling,
he could've lived a long life.

22
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:49,770
Luffy could never have been
killed by someone like you!

23
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:56,870
Well, you're alive and able to wail
thanks to your friends' sacrifice.

24
00:03:56,870 --> 00:04:01,930
They deserve your deepest gratitude,
so at least the dead can...

25
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:04,350
Where's Luffy?!

26
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:07,410
Why are you here?!

27
00:04:10,510 --> 00:04:12,610
...rest in peace.

28
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:19,450
Medi Assembly Hall
Alubarna North Block

29
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:17,590
Damn that idiot! Where the hell did she go?

30
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,450
This is why I said to shut up and hide.

31
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:23,910
She does nothing but
slow me down. Dumb woman!

32
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:34,670
That's it, I can't run anymore!
I'll have to fight!

33
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:41,590
No way!

34
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:44,560
We're not getting anywhere.

35
00:04:46,310 --> 00:04:47,270
He's so impatient.

36
00:04:55,180 --> 00:04:55,730
Zoro!

37
00:05:01,580 --> 00:05:03,280
The stone post split vertically!

38
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:09,580
Mr. 1 and Miss Doublefinger

39
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:09,580
vs

40
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:09,580
Roronoa Zoro and Nami

41
00:05:05,810 --> 00:05:09,390
Split? No, it didn't.

42
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,830
That was clearly
the work of a swordsman.

43
00:05:14,980 --> 00:05:15,590
Move.

44
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:23,530
You sliced it, didn't you?
With those arms?

45
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,980
That's a rather odd body
you've got there, isn't it?

46
00:05:30,020 --> 00:05:35,670
Indeed it is. I ate the Dice-Dice Fruit,
so any part of me can become a blade.

47
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:37,050
You're him, aren't you?

48
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:40,240
The swordsman rumored to have
cut down 100 men at Whisky Peak?

49
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:46,060
The pirate who declined Baroque Works' invite
several years ago in the East Blue

50
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:49,250
and eliminated the former Mr. 7...

51
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,040
...is you, right?

52
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:54,500
Ha! There's a story
that takes me back.

53
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:59,250
That was your fault
for not accepting my terms.

54
00:05:59,710 --> 00:06:03,260
I told your scout man back then:

55
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:06,930
"I will join if you make me your boss."

56
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:10,020
Such a funny man.

57
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:14,090
Instead of meeting my terms,
he slashed at me.

58
00:06:14,090 --> 00:06:15,950
I just put him in his place.

59
00:06:16,650 --> 00:06:18,730
Would you like to try
inviting me, too?

60
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:23,580
But you guys are such a joke now,
I wouldn't agree to even be your boss.

61
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:31,390
You're making quite
a mockery of me, huh?

62
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:37,420
You, a swordsman from
a small-time band of pirates.

63
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:41,540
That may be so, but who
do you think you guys are?

64
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:44,290
Puppets, without will of your own,

65
00:06:44,290 --> 00:06:46,940
baited into creating
a utopia in name only?

66
00:06:46,940 --> 00:06:49,800
Or are you really just tin soldiers...

67
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:53,940
without any substance?

68
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:56,310
Miss Doublefinger...

69
00:06:56,940 --> 00:07:00,190
You're going to tell me
that this one is yours, right?

70
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:04,360
Do as you please.
I'll deal with the girl.

71
00:07:04,990 --> 00:07:06,080
Hey, Nami!

72
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,390
She's gone!

73
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:30,430
Even here, I can still hear
the sounds of battle.

74
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,090
So she wasn't able to stop
the Rebel Army at the entrance.

75
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,850
I wonder if Vivi
and the others are okay.

76
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:41,640
They're all... fighting
with their very lives.

77
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,770
And yet... I'm...

78
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:55,290
Like I said... I want a more
powerful weapon too!

79
00:07:55,650 --> 00:08:00,410
Powerful weapon? What's
the point of you being strong?

80
00:08:00,410 --> 00:08:05,530
It's true that I'm not a fighter,
but I have a nice figure. And I'm cute.

81
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:06,670
Huh? I don't follow.

82
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:07,990
But I still...

83
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:13,280
want to be at least strong enough
not to cause the others trouble.

84
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,840
Especially this time, for Vivi.

85
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:40,790
Usopp... you can understand
how I feel, can't you?

86
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,710
We're different from them.

87
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
KoJXxnJOIX

88
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
YDZLTnBrny

89
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
SyrdeNQOmY

90
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
hnOSJNHoOT

91
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
gWKZbsxDEX

92
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
iUYjRFTECw

93
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
eoHmvxeIBt

94
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:58,430
RDKUjcbNnW

95
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:48,320
They're as strong as monsters.

96
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:52,330
They can fight against any enemy
using only their own might.

97
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:57,120
But you and I are
ordinary humans with no power.

98
00:08:57,640 --> 00:09:02,100
Once the battle starts,
we only panic in shame.

99
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:05,860
We'll just be a burden to the others,
unable to protect even ourselves.

100
00:09:08,070 --> 00:09:10,950
If the situation arises
where we want to join the fight,

101
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,660
all we can do is rely
on powerful weapons... right?

102
00:09:20,580 --> 00:09:23,750
The reason you frantically work
on inventing weapons

103
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:29,630
is because you want to feel pride
that you can fight like the others, isn't it?

104
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:36,470
Me too! I want to fight
with my own two hands, for Vivi!

105
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:37,680
So help me!

106
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,690
There's barely time
before we get to Alabasta.

107
00:09:46,170 --> 00:09:50,490
Yeah... Also, there's no way
that I can get strong just like that.

108
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:52,890
I'm sorry for being absurd.

109
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:56,160
Who says it's absurd
just 'cause we lack time?

110
00:09:59,210 --> 00:10:02,790
Are you suggesting there's something
the Unbelievable Usopp can't do?

111
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:04,750
Then...

112
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,000
you're gonna do it?!

113
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
KoJXxnJOIX

114
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
YDZLTnBrny

115
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
SyrdeNQOmY

116
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
hnOSJNHoOT

117
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
gWKZbsxDEX

118
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
iUYjRFTECw

119
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
eoHmvxeIBt

120
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:14,510
RDKUjcbNnW

121
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,830
Oh, I love you! Thank you, Usopp!

122
00:10:10,830 --> 00:10:12,760
Now, to be direct, the material cost–

123
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,010
Thank you, really!

124
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:18,060
Hey, hey, hey... It's not like weapons
can be created for free.

125
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,820
Well, I'm counting on you!

126
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,020
Hey, listen to me!

127
00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:23,630
You guys are off the hook now.

128
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:28,610
Nami...

129
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:44,000
What am I doing...
letting that noise scare me?

130
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:48,490
And after I grandly boasted
in front of Usopp.

131
00:10:48,490 --> 00:10:50,460
I'm prepared, aren't I?

132
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,430
To fight for Vivi.

133
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:05,520
That's right... Usopp kept his promise.

134
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:07,680
I just have to fight!

135
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:10,600
If it's just that woman,
I should be able to...

136
00:11:35,150 --> 00:11:37,800
It's no use running, girl.

137
00:11:38,690 --> 00:11:42,310
Miss Doublefinger! What was that
spear-like weapon she just used?

138
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:45,480
Does she also have devil fruit powers?

139
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,980
Do you get it now?

140
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:53,570
I'm a spike person with
Spike-Spike Fruit powers.

141
00:11:53,570 --> 00:11:57,070
I can create spikes from
anywhere on my body.

142
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,640
Spikes that can easily pierce
through stone walls...

143
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:04,950
If I get cornered even once, her spikes will
pierce me all over, and I'll be finished.

144
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:09,250
Oh? The poor thing is
getting up to fight me.

145
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:10,960
That's right!

146
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:18,050
Sometimes, it calls forth clouds.
Other times, it makes rain fall.

147
00:12:18,050 --> 00:12:20,550
And occasionally, it produces wind!

148
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:24,520
This miraculous baton causes
catastrophes when it's rearranged!

149
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:30,980
You're done for! My new weapon
—the Climate Baton!

150
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:32,690
What... in the world...?

151
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,230
First, sunny weather!

152
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:35,850
Fine Tempo!

153
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:42,890
Wow, amazing! Doves flew out!

154
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:45,460
That was stupid!

155
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,540
Are you... okay?

156
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,920
The initial attack often goes this way.

157
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:58,790
We start by lowering
the enemy's guard, right?

158
00:12:58,790 --> 00:12:59,880
I get it, Usopp.

159
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,630
This time, you're finished!

160
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:03,760
Cloudy Tempo!

161
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:08,430
Wow! What pretty flowers!

162
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:11,760
No way I can win like this!

163
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:18,240
I don't know her situation...
but what a poor child.

164
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,030
Hurry up! Princess Vivi is in danger!

165
00:13:24,420 --> 00:13:27,910
Cannons! Bring the cannons here!
Destroy the gate!

166
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:28,750
Quickly!

167
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,850
Dieciséis Fleurs!

168
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:43,590
What the...?

169
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:14,390
I hope we can have
some peace and quiet now.

170
00:14:41,820 --> 00:14:43,360
What a stubborn girl.

171
00:14:47,530 --> 00:14:49,970
Why put so much effort
into dodging my attacks?

172
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:52,370
You have no chance.

173
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:54,960
You're wrong!

174
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:58,740
According to the instructions,
this baton can do way more than that!

175
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:05,010
Now, be a good girl
and stay right there.

176
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:07,800
Then I can kill you without
causing you much pain.

177
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:13,180
So, you're still putting on
your little magic show?

178
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,430
The weather forecast shows thunder!

179
00:15:16,430 --> 00:15:17,690
Thunder Tempo!

180
00:15:26,590 --> 00:15:30,420
Thunder Tempo...
Thunder Tempo... Thunder...

181
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:33,200
Stinger Finger!

182
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:43,480
No!

183
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:53,490
My cheek is bleeding!

184
00:15:54,210 --> 00:15:57,730
Ahh... I wonder if
I'm gonna die like this.

185
00:15:58,130 --> 00:16:00,730
I'm gonna die? I'm gonna die!

186
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:07,220
If I die, I'm gonna curse him.
That long nose...! Long Nose!

187
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:09,530
Couldn't he have made
an actual weapo...

188
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:11,580
Wait.

189
00:16:12,490 --> 00:16:16,080
Well, then... I'll kill you now, okay?

190
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:27,720
She's standing on the underside
of the bridge! How?!

191
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,930
Stinger Hedgehog!

192
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:34,930
That was close!

193
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,100
H-H-Hey, hold on! Stop!

194
00:16:40,410 --> 00:16:42,780
I said hold on! Hold on a bit!

195
00:16:42,780 --> 00:16:45,860
A minute! Would you
give me a minute?! Hey!

196
00:16:47,660 --> 00:16:49,200
She'll catch me out in the open!

197
00:16:58,470 --> 00:17:01,250
This is it! You're skewered!

198
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:04,380
No... thank you!

199
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:18,790
Well...

200
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:26,360
it seems that when it comes
to battles... she isn't a total amateur.

201
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,650
What was that?

202
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:32,910
Something in here
caught my eye earlier.

203
00:17:32,910 --> 00:17:35,860
I have this sneaking suspicion...

204
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:36,870
Where was that?

205
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:38,360
That's it!

206
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:45,170
The techniques written above
are sure to heat up any party!

207
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,050
You've gotta be kidding me!

208
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:54,800
Also, I'll write the configurations
for battle on the back.

209
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:56,610
The back?

210
00:18:04,130 --> 00:18:07,610
Now then... I wonder where
you're hiding this time...

211
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:09,230
little kitty?

212
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,170
I won't run or hide anymore.

213
00:18:19,170 --> 00:18:23,500
I may not look it, but in my eight years
as a thief, I survived life-or-death crises...

214
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:26,210
all by myself!

215
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:32,760
I can't stand being treated
like just an ordinary girl.

216
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:36,390
Really... I'm sorry, then.

217
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:39,010
What's got you so
confident all of a sudden?

218
00:18:39,260 --> 00:18:41,770
Listen up! I'll show you
my real skills now!

219
00:18:43,140 --> 00:18:45,230
The baton's battle configurations...

220
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:48,750
First, understand the characteristics
of the three segments.

221
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:53,400
Each of them can shoot off
air bubbles by shaking or blowing.

222
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:55,690
The first one shoots off hot air...

223
00:18:58,890 --> 00:19:00,650
a heat ball!

224
00:19:00,650 --> 00:19:02,870
What is this? It feels warm.

225
00:19:03,370 --> 00:19:05,040
The next one shoots off cool air...

226
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,840
a cool ball!

227
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:10,670
Ah, it feels cool.

228
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:13,270
And the last one
shoots off electricity...

229
00:19:15,470 --> 00:19:17,080
a thunder ball!

230
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:19,130
Oh, no. That tingled.

231
00:19:19,130 --> 00:19:24,060
These techniques aren't complete yet,
so if you use them at parties...

232
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:25,270
Then don't list them!

233
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:28,800
Are you satisfied?

234
00:19:33,180 --> 00:19:35,070
Sewing Stinger!

235
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:40,480
Please, something I can use...!
Abilities that aren't just for amusement...!

236
00:19:45,710 --> 00:19:47,710
I'm sorry.

237
00:19:47,710 --> 00:19:49,670
Enough playing around!

238
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,300
Stinger Step!

239
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:10,800
Oh, I get it! The heat ball
and the cool ball...!

240
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:14,790
When they stop spinning,
the air bubbles collide, create air flow,

241
00:20:14,790 --> 00:20:17,030
and cause a tremendous wind!

242
00:20:17,030 --> 00:20:18,830
This is incredible, Usopp!

243
00:20:18,830 --> 00:20:21,470
The cyclone tempo
is like an ordinary boomerang.

244
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:24,310
After the party, you can all
go outside and use it to play...

245
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:26,580
He doesn't seem
to understand it himself...

246
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:30,860
But with this, I might be able to...

247
00:20:33,460 --> 00:20:35,590
She's using a strange weapon!

248
00:20:36,710 --> 00:20:38,800
Pay attention to the fight!

249
00:20:41,110 --> 00:20:43,970
To show your back to your
enemy during the battle...

250
00:20:43,970 --> 00:20:46,220
Don't you see this is
a fight to the death?

251
00:21:00,180 --> 00:21:03,370
I changed the air density
using the cool ball.

252
00:21:03,370 --> 00:21:06,150
A bent light refraction
from a huge temperature swing...

253
00:21:06,150 --> 00:21:06,910
In other words...

254
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:11,630
A mirage! That's not...
Over such a short distance!

255
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:21,680
We can't win with power—
so survive by using your brain!

256
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:24,550
That's how we fight, right?!

257
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:27,930
If I use it efficiently,
even a miracle can happen!

258
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,730
Looks like this is
the perfect weapon for me!

259
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:37,420
Now I've figured out
the Climate Baton!

260
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:39,630
Give up while you can!

261
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:43,320
Southeast Gate, Alubarna

262
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:47,700
So you're still alive, at least.

263
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:51,570
– Sanji!
– Sanji!

264
00:21:51,570 --> 00:21:52,880
Those wounds...

265
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:56,840
So, how'd the battle
with Mr. 2 turn out?

266
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:59,630
What do you think? Here...

267
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:02,600
Ahhh! My goggles!

268
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:07,060
So you got them back
from him! Thanks, Sanji!

269
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:10,870
You're such a... Ahh!
Hey, wait a sec! They're broken!

270
00:22:10,870 --> 00:22:14,410
You bastard! This is
the North Blue's newest model!

271
00:22:14,410 --> 00:22:17,270
Do you know how valuable
these goggles are?

272
00:22:17,270 --> 00:22:18,670
Hey, look at that.

273
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:19,970
Listen to me...

274
00:22:19,970 --> 00:22:20,900
Ah!

275
00:22:21,490 --> 00:22:24,430
That must be reinforcements
for the Rebel Army.

276
00:22:25,050 --> 00:22:26,580
So there'll be more of them?

277
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:31,080
Looks like it. I guess Vivi
couldn't stop the Rebel Army.

278
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:34,340
Ah, dammit!

279
00:22:33,670 --> 00:22:34,340
Vaaa.

280
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:36,040
Hm? Vaaa?

281
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:39,630
Hey, where have you
been hiding, Eyelashes?!

282
00:22:40,490 --> 00:22:44,390
Let's hurry to the palace.
Maybe we can still assist Vivi.

283
00:22:44,390 --> 00:22:45,240
Okay!

284
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:46,550
Hey, Usopp! Let's go already!

285
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:49,600
Y-Yeah! Ah, hey, Eyelashes!
Let me get on!

286
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,310
Look! Can't you see these wounds?

287
00:22:52,310 --> 00:22:54,270
Eyelashes! Stop! Let me get on!

288
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:57,230
Father!

289
00:23:00,470 --> 00:23:03,360
Let His Majesty go, Crocodile!

290
00:23:05,750 --> 00:23:07,520
I'm sorry, Vivi...

291
00:23:08,110 --> 00:23:15,100
I failed to leverage the intel
you risked your life to obtain.

292
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:16,460
Father...

293
00:23:23,890 --> 00:23:28,370
Let me tell you right away.
I don't plan to keep you or your father alive.

294
00:23:28,950 --> 00:23:34,180
When a kingdom dies out, it's just natural
for its royal family to follow suit.

295
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,610
However, before I take the throne,

296
00:23:37,610 --> 00:23:44,150
there's something that I need
to ask of you, the current king.

297
00:23:45,950 --> 00:23:49,870
In fact, this is indeed
my most crucial goal...

298
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:55,540
Cobra... Where is Pluton?

299
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:09,500
You... How do you know that name?
